        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ci): raise exact-review admission caps",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- raise exact-review durable queue admission from 14 to 20 concurrent leases\n- raise per-target exact-review admission from 10 to 16 so OpenClaw backlog can use idle worker budget\n- wire the new per-target limit into checked-in automation limits, dashboard worker defaults, wrangler vars, docs, and drift checks\n\n## Why\n\nLive queue telemetry showed ~30 pending exact reviews while the global worker budget was only about half used. The queue was constrained by exact-review admission caps, not Blacksmith or GitHub runner registration.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm run build:repair`\n- `pnpm run build:dashboard`\n- `pnpm run check:limits`\n- `node --test test/dashboard-worker.test.ts test/repair/workflow-utils.test.ts`\n",
